</nav></header><main aria-label="main content"><div class="speakable">
      <b data-is-speakable>COVID-19 Threatens Food Supply Chain As Farms Worry About Workers Falling Ill</b>   <b data-is-speakable>COVID-19 has turned one end of the food industry — stores and restaurants — on its head. At the other end, food production hums along as usual, but that could change if workers catch the virus.</b>
</div>
<div id="wrapper">
      <header class="contentheader contentheader--one" data-metrics='{"category":"The Coronavirus Crisis"}' ><div class="branding branding--seamus">
      <a href="https://www.npr.org/series/812054919/the-coronavirus-crisis" data-metrics='{"action":"click branding"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/03/11/c_virus_outbreak_sq-428f510423dae3e930089eb9efa735f4c6b8d9f3-s100-c85.jpg" class="branding__image-promo"  alt="The novel coronavirus, first detected at the end of 2019, has caused a global pandemic." /><div class="branding__inner">
      <b class='branding__lead-in branding__lead-in--series'>Special Series</b>   <h2 class="branding__title">The Coronavirus Crisis</h2>
   <b class="branding__mini-teaser">Everything you need to know about the global outbreak</b>
</div>

